<subSubSection id="C351F896890DFF8C97CEFA96FB346AEC" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF4AB1D890DFF8C97CEFA96FB346AEC" blockId="50.[128,654,1350,1754]" lastBlockId="50.[701,1228,712,1540]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
DIAGNOSIS: Small, compact, dark-bodied acalyptrates with generally a metallic shine on the frons, scutum, and abdominal tergites. Head with minute pair of postocellar setae, generally 3 pairs of fronto-orbital setae (anteriormost pair inclinate); arista bare or minutely setulose, pedicel with dorsal seam. Scutum with 2 pairs of dorsocentrals, approximately 4 rows acrostichals. Wings with distinctive venation: Vein C with break near Sc, weakened near h (but no humeral break, contra 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C962DF9BAFDB66FFC" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[377,516,1642,1666]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="205 - 225" refId="ref26337" refString="Hardy, D. E. 1980. Xenasteiidae, a new family of Schizophora (Diptera) from the Pacific and Indian Oceans. Proceedings of the Hawaiian Entomological Society 23: 205 - 225." type="journal article" year="1980">Hardy, 1980</bibRefCitation>
); R 
<subScript id="17CFA958890DFF8C957EF9A5FDFA6FFB" attach="left" box="[554,584,1652,1669]" fontSize="7" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">2+3</subScript>
short; vein M past level where R 
<subScript id="17CFA958890DFF8C96F8F942FE786FDC" attach="left" box="[428,458,1682,1698]" fontSize="7" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript id="17CFA958890DFF8C9548F942FD886FDC" attach="left" box="[540,570,1682,1698]" fontSize="7" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">4+5</subScript>
fork is evanescent, represented by row of microtrichia; Cu present, incomplete; anal veins lost. Male terminalia distinctive but uniform: with pair of large lobes on posterior margin of hypandrium, which project posteriad and bear apical pair of minute, spinelike setulae; pair of long, projecting surstyli also present; aedeagus small, mostly membranous; male pregenital sclerites asymmetrical, well developed (tVII?) on right side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C351F896890DFF8C958CFC48FB3C6F7A" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF4AB1D890DFF8C958CFC48FB3C6F7A" blockId="50.[701,1228,712,1540]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
COMMENTS: Based on the collecting data, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BD09E890DFF8C95E9FC66FCD56AB0" box="[701,871,950,974]" class="Insecta" family="Xenasteiidae" genus="Xenasteia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93F770F890DFF8C95E9FC66FC986AB0" box="[701,810,950,974]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Xenasteia</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
appear to be associated with xeric, sandy habitats, particularly seashores and near-shore habitats. They commonly come to light (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C9456FBDFFC216D59" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[770,915,1039,1063]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="205 - 225" refId="ref26337" refString="Hardy, D. E. 1980. Xenasteiidae, a new family of Schizophora (Diptera) from the Pacific and Indian Oceans. Proceedings of the Hawaiian Entomological Society 23: 205 - 225." type="journal article" year="1980">Hardy, 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C94F6FBDFFB9C6D59" author="Ismay, J. W." box="[930,1070,1039,1063]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="41 - 46" refId="ref26374" refString="Ismay, J. W. 2003. New species and records of Xenasteiidae (Diptera) from the Australian and Oceanian regions. Bishop Museum Occasional Papers 73: 41 - 46." type="journal article" year="2003">Ismay, 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C9368FBDFFB0D6D59" author="Papp, L." box="[1084,1215,1039,1063]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="187 - 213" refId="ref26861" refString="Papp, L. 2005. Some acalyptrate flies from Taiwan. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientarum Hungaricae 51: 187 - 213." type="journal article" year="2005">Papp, 2005</bibRefCitation>
), and congregate on xeric vegetation, but also have been found on decaying fish (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C936EFB9BFB756D1D" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[1082,1223,1099,1123]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="205 - 225" refId="ref26337" refString="Hardy, D. E. 1980. Xenasteiidae, a new family of Schizophora (Diptera) from the Pacific and Indian Oceans. Proceedings of the Hawaiian Entomological Society 23: 205 - 225." type="journal article" year="1980">Hardy, 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C95E9FBB9FCF86DFF" author="Ismay, J. W." box="[701,842,1129,1153]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="41 - 46" refId="ref26374" refString="Ismay, J. W. 2003. New species and records of Xenasteiidae (Diptera) from the Australian and Oceanian regions. Bishop Museum Occasional Papers 73: 41 - 46." type="journal article" year="2003">Ismay, 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The vegetation from which they have been collected are tamarisk (
<taxonomicName id="4C4BD09E890DFF8C9337FB57FB706DE1" box="[1123,1218,1159,1183]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F770F890DFF8C9337FB57FB706DE1" box="[1123,1218,1159,1183]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Tamarix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) trees (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C945FFB74FC786DC2" author="Freidberg, A." box="[779,970,1188,1212]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="133 - 137" refId="ref26222" refString="Freidberg, A. 1994. A new Palearctic species of Xenasteia Hardy (Diptera: Xenasteiidae). Israel Journal of Entomology 28: 133 - 137." type="journal article" year="1994">Freidberg, 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C94B5FB74FB0D6DC2" author="Carles-Tolra, M." box="[993,1215,1188,1212]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 2" refId="ref26033" refString="Carles-Tolra, M. 1995. A new dipterous family to Europe (Diptera: Xenasteiidae). Boletin de la Asociacion Espanola de Entomologia 19: 1 - 2." type="journal article" year="1995">Carles-Tolrá, 1995</bibRefCitation>
), 
<emphasis id="B93F770F890DFF8C95E9FB12FC526DA4" box="[701,992,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Chrithanemum maritimum</emphasis>
stems (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C936FFB12FB0D6DA4" author="Papp, L." box="[1083,1215,1218,1242]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="415 - 431" refId="ref26818" refString="Papp, L. 1980. New taxa of the acalyptrate flies (Diptera: Tunisimyiidae fam. n., Risidae, Ephydridae: Nannodastiinae subfam. n.). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 26: 415 - 431." type="journal article" year="1980">Papp, 1980</bibRefCitation>
), and decaying leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BD09E890DFF8C94EDFB30FB916D86" box="[953,1059,1248,1272]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F770F890DFF8C94EDFB30FB916D86" box="[953,1059,1248,1272]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Pandanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C4BD09E890DFF8C9364FB30FB766D86" box="[1072,1220,1248,1272]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Pandanaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C9591FB2DFCEA6C6B" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[709,856,1277,1301]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="205 - 225" refId="ref26337" refString="Hardy, D. E. 1980. Xenasteiidae, a new family of Schizophora (Diptera) from the Pacific and Indian Oceans. Proceedings of the Hawaiian Entomological Society 23: 205 - 225." type="journal article" year="1980">Hardy, 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAD6EC890DFF8C943CFB2DFC456C6B" author="Ismay, J. W." box="[872,1015,1277,1301]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="41 - 46" refId="ref26374" refString="Ismay, J. W. 2003. New species and records of Xenasteiidae (Diptera) from the Australian and Oceanian regions. Bishop Museum Occasional Papers 73: 41 - 46." type="journal article" year="2003">Ismay, 2003</bibRefCitation>
). These plants are associated with saline and maritime habitats. Interestingly, the new 
<collectingCountry id="F35CEB8D890DFF8C9495FAE9FC5A6C2F" box="[961,1000,1337,1361]" name="Fiji" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fiji</collectingCountry>
species is probably the only one to have been collected using Malaise traps, but from a unique environment in 
<collectingCountry id="F35CEB8D890DFF8C958DFA42FCB16CD4" box="[729,771,1426,1450]" name="Fiji" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fiji</collectingCountry>
: the Sigatoka Sand Dunes, of which large stands of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BD09E890DFF8C9460FA60FC2C6CB6" box="[820,926,1456,1480]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F770F890DFF8C9460FA60FC2C6CB6" box="[820,926,1456,1480]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Pandanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur nearby. Systematic collecting at Sigatoka using light traps will probably yield a large series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BD09E890DFF8C9349FA3CFB356F7A" authorityName="Hardy" authorityYear="1980" box="[1053,1159,1516,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Xenasteiidae" genus="Xenasteia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F770F890DFF8C9349FA3CFB356F7A" box="[1053,1159,1516,1540]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Xenasteia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
